Every time when I&#x27;m trying to merge something I get this error:

{code}
#!php

{
  "error":  {
    "message": "name, email or commit message not provided",
    "id": "2e891a5abd1c4af8aa8528bf986009ba"
  }
}
{code}

I&#x27;m using this link:

{code}
#!

https://bitbucket.org/api/2.0/repositories/***/***/pullrequests/35/merge
{code}

Can somebody help me?

Currently Bitbucket splits repository lists into pages, no more than 25 items per page. This may be a personal taste, but that kind of pagination is totally useless, because:

* current paginated repository list ruins dashboard&#x27;s appearance as it is significantly shorter than the feed to the right;
* it is convenient to see all repositories at once (and Ctrl+F them if necessary);
* that paging requires users to wait until Ajax request competes and thus irritates them.

Full repository list is almost never too long not to fit in page or take too much time to load, so it may be a better option to just put all repositories in a single non-paginated list.

Those {{staff}}, {{repo owner}} and {{reporter}} labels are good in issue comments next to commenter&#x27;s name but at least one case is missing: users with admin/write access to repo via teams or groups. At least public repositories could benefit from this.

For example:

* repo owner: {{team1}}
* repo creator: {{user1}}
* users with admin access via group: {{group1}}
* users with write access via group: {{group2}}

Currently when {{user1}} or a member of {{group1}} or {{group2}} comments on an issue, no additional label is attached next to his name. I don&#x27;t know how user rights works for {{user1}} but at least members of {{group1}} or {{group2}} can make changes in repo and therefore they could be highlighted as well (with {{repo crew}} or whatever).

